# ChefMate Environment Variables Example
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values

# =============================================================================
# OpenAI API Configuration (REQUIRED)
# =============================================================================
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Note: Keep this key secure and never commit it to version control
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key-here

# =============================================================================
# Application URL (OPTIONAL)
# =============================================================================
# Used for generating absolute URLs in metadata and sitemaps
# Default: http://localhost:3000 (development)
# Production: Set this to your deployed URL (e.g., https://chefmate.app)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# =============================================================================
# Vercel Analytics (AUTOMATIC)
# =============================================================================
# Vercel Analytics and Speed Insights are automatically enabled when deployed to Vercel
# No environment variables needed - they are configured via the Vercel dashboard
# Local development: Analytics will not send data
# Learn more: https://vercel.com/docs/analytics

# =============================================================================
# Development Settings (OPTIONAL)
# =============================================================================
# Node environment (automatically set by Next.js)
# NODE_ENV=development

# =============================================================================
# Rate Limiting (CONFIGURED IN CODE)
# =============================================================================
# Rate limiting is currently configured in the API route code
# Default: 15 recipes per hour per IP address
# To modify: Edit src/app/api/recipe/generate/route.ts

# =============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.local.example .env.local
# 2. Get an OpenAI API key from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# 3. Replace "sk-your-openai-api-key-here" with your actual API key
# 4. (Optional) Set NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL to your deployment URL
# 5. Run: pnpm dev
# 6. Visit: http://localhost:3000

# =============================================================================
# Security Notes
# =============================================================================
# - NEVER commit .env.local to version control (it's in .gitignore)
# - Keep your OpenAI API key secure
# - Rotate keys if accidentally exposed
# - Monitor usage at https://platform.openai.com/usage
# - Set up billing alerts to prevent unexpected charges

# =============================================================================
# Cost Management
# =============================================================================
# OpenAI API costs vary by model:
# - GPT-4o: ~$0.005 per recipe generation (recommended for quality)
# - GPT-4o-mini: ~$0.0001 per recipe generation (cost-effective)
#
# Rate limiting (15/hour) helps control costs
# Monitor usage: https://platform.openai.com/usage
# Set up billing limits: https://platform.openai.com/account/billing/limits
